label.value: increased level of transport gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more transport RNAs measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells). Transport RNAs are transcribed from genes whose products are involved in one or more transport processes.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: decreased nucleosome occupancy

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosome occupancy is lower than normal at one or more specific sites. Nucleosome occupancy measures the tendency for DNA in a given region to be packaged into nucleosomes.

label.value: abnormal RNA 5'-end processing

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which formation of the mature 5' end of an RNA molecule is abnormal.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, single cell division, small cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that undergoes a single round of cell division to produce daughter cells that are smaller than normal, which then die.

label.value: inviable branched, swollen, elongated vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is inviable, branched, septated, and has a larger volume and is longer, than normal. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

label.value: inviable branched, swollen, elongated, multiseptate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is inviable, branched, has more than one septum, and has a larger volume and is longer, than normal. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

label.value: small multiseptate cell during stationary phase

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell is smaller than normal and contains more than one septum, when the cell is in a culture in stationary phase.

label.value: small binucleate cell during stationary phase

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell is smaller than normal and contains two nuclei, when the cell is in a culture in stationary phase.

label.value: normal positive regulation of DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which positive regulation of DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal DNA polymerase processivity factor activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the rate or occurrence of DNA polymerase processivity factor activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased DNA polymerase processivity factor activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the rate or occurrence of DNA polymerase processivity factor activity is decreased.

label.value: normal DNA polymerase processivity factor activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the rate and occurrence of DNA polymerase processivity factor activity are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal positive regulation of ATPase activity

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which positive regulation of an ATPase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased cellular HMW ubiquitin conjugate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein having high molecular mass due to polyubiquitin conjugation is greater than normal.

label.value: normal proteasome localization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which proteasome localization is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal nucleolar chromatin organization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleolar chromatin organization is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal nucleolar chromatin organization resulting in peripheral chromatin distribution

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleolar chromatin organization is abnormal, such that nucleolar chromatin is distributed in a ring-shaped structure around the nuclear periphery rather than in a crescent-shaped structure on one side of the nucleus.

label.value: abolished centromeric DNA separation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic sister chromatid separation does not occur at the centromeric regions. The remainder of the sister chromatids may or may not separate.

label.value: abolished rDNA separation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic sister chromatid separation does not occur at the rDNA repeat regions. The remainder of the sister chromatids may or may not separate.

label.value: abnormal spindle assembly during meiosis II

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which assembly of the meiotic spindle is abnormal during the second meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: long curved interphase microtubules

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form cytoplasmic microtubules that are longer than normal and are curved, i.e. follow a smooth bend rather than a straight line, during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: In severe instances of this phenotype, microtubules grow long enough to curve around the cell tip.

label.value: sensitive to EGTA

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to EGTA. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of EGTA that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: resistance to latrunculin A

value.value: An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of latrunculin A than normal.

label.value: abnormal chromosome morphology, indistinct DNA

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which DNA is not visible in a distinct structure corresponding to the nucleus, but is instead diffuse or not visible at all.

label.value: decreased number of Rad52 foci during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Rad52 (also called Rad22) accumulates is lower than normal.

label.value: viable vegetative cell enlarged around nucleus

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is viable and has a diameter larger than normal only near the middle of the cell, around the nucleus.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, multiple cell divisions, branched, curved, elongated cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that is elongated and branched (and septated) and is curved along the long axis, and undergoes two or more rounds of cell division and then dies.

label.value: abnormal DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate or other catalytic property of a DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased DNA-directed DNA polymerase processivity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed processivity of a DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity is lower than normal. Processivity refers to the number of nucleotides incorporated into a nascent DNA strand per polymerase-DNA binding event.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, single or double cell division, branched, elongated cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that is elongated and branched (and septated), and undergoes one or two rounds of cell division and then dies.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, single or double cell division, branched, curved, elongated cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that is elongated and branched (and septated) and is curved along the long axis, and undergoes one or two rounds of cell division and then dies.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, single or double cell division, curved, elongated cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that is elongated and is curved along the long axis, and undergoes one or two rounds of cell division and then dies.

label.value: decreased number of Rad54 foci during cellular response to doxorubicin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Rad54 (also called Rhp54) accumulates is lower than normal during a cellular response to doxorubicin.

label.value: abnormal membrane organization during mating

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cellular membrane organization is abnormal during mating.

label.value: abnormal regulation of transcription

value.value: A transcription regulation phenotype in which any process of regulation of transcription is abnormal.

label.value: abnormal regulation of transcription during vegetative growth

value.value: A transcription regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which any process of regulation of transcription is abnormal.

definition.value: This is a high-level term whose primary purpose is to organize terms beneath it in the ontology, and we expect that it will not be used for direct annotations. Please consider using a more specific term to annotate each phenotype. There may be enough evidence to support annotation to a more specific term such as 'abnormal chromatin silencing' (FYPO:0000144); if not, it is safer to annotate to 'increased transcription during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000780) or 'decreased transcription during vegetative growth' (FYPO:0000781) rather than explicitly claiming that an effect on regulation was observed.

label.value: abnormal mitochondrial translation

value.value: A metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrial translation is abnormal.

definition.value: Note that this term should be used only when an experiment measures protein synthesis directly, e.g. by measuring incorporation of a radiolabeled amino acid. Consider annotating to 'altered protein level' (FYPO:0000834) or one of its descendants.

label.value: normal mitochondrial translation

value.value: A metabolism phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrial translation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: Note that this term should be used only when an experiment measures protein synthesis directly, e.g. by measuring incorporation of a radiolabeled amino acid.

label.value: abolished mitochondrial translation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitochondrial translation does not occur.

definition.value: Note that this term should be used only when an experiment measures mitochondrial protein synthesis directly, e.g. by measuring incorporation of a radiolabeled amino acid. Consider annotating to 'decreased protein level' (FYPO:0000835) or one of its descendants.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, single or double cell division, small cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce a cell that is smaller than normal and undergoes one or two rounds of cell division.

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic M phase with abnormal spindle

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in M phase under conditions where arrest does not normally occur, and the position or morphology of the mitotic spindle is abnormal.

definition.value: Metaphase is defined as the part of mitosis when chromosomes are aligned in the middle of the spindle. If no spindle is present, do not use this term, but consider 'abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic prophase' (FYPO:0003145). If you cannot tell whether a spindle is present, or if metaphase cannot be clearly detected, annotate to the more general term 'abnormal cell cycle arrest in mitotic M phase' (FYPO:0000608).

label.value: normal cell wall beta-glucan level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of beta-D-glucan measured in the cell wall is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: premature ascospore release from ascus

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of ascospore release from an ascus begins earlier than normal.

label.value: inviable small spore with abnormal shape

value.value: A viability phenotype in which a spore is unable to survive under conditions in which wild type spores survive, and has a smaller volume than normal and an abnormal shape. An inviable spore does not germinate.

label.value: abnormal response to mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint signaling

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a mitotic cell cycle arrest that normally occurs in response to mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint signaling is abnormal (does not occur, or occurs abnormally). Abnormal arrest may result from a problem with detection of conditions that normally trigger a checkpoint, transduction of the checkpoint signal, or the response to the checkpoint signal.

label.value: mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint override

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a mitotic cell cycle arrest that normally occurs in response to mitotic cell cycle spindle assembly checkpoint signaling does not occur. As a result, the septation initiation network (SIN) signaling pathway is activated despite activation of the mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint (SAC). Normally, under conditions that activate the SAC, SIN activation is inhibited and the cell cycle arrests in anaphase. In this phenotype, premature SIN activation leads to premature cytokinesis and the formation of cut cells.

label.value: microtubules present in increased numbers

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain more microtubules than normal.

label.value: short interphase microtubules present in increased numbers

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains more, and shorter, cytoplasmic microtubules than normal during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: increased chromatin silencing

value.value: A transcription regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing is incrsasd. Chromatin silencing is the observed effect of processes that repress transcription in a region of the genome that is normally assembled into heterochromatin or CENP-A-containing chromatin (the latter is found at the centromere central core).

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin or CENP-A-containing chromatin. See the GO cellular component terms 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792) and 'CENP-A containing chromatin' (GO:0061638), and the biological process terms 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828) and 'CENP-A containing chromatin organization' (GO:0061641).

label.value: increased chromatin silencing at centromere inner repeat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which chromatin silencing at centromere inner repeat regions is increased.

definition.value: Chromatin silencing phenotypes may reflect the assembly or maintenance of heterochromatin. See the GO cellular component term 'heterochromatin' (GO:0000792), and the biological process term 'heterochromatin organization' (GO:0070828).
